ETSU015791

! J. Donaldson June 2011 (Handwritten)
PLANTS OF BUFFALO MOUNTAIN, EAST TENNESSEE

*Galax urceolata*
Diapensiaceae

Washington County, TN
Buffalo Mountain, 5070 High Ridge Rd. approx. ½ mile up
the Service Road on the right side. This plant is abundant
throughout the park and prefers moist or dry woodlands on
acidic soils.
2300 ft.

Stemless, evergreen perennial with flowering stalks 18-24 in.
tall. Leaves are basal, 2-6 in. wide, circular to ovate. Flowers
are white, and numerous in a tall raceme or spike.

Reference: Wildflowers of TN p. 132
Ryan N. Dixon                      5/25/11
#10

John C. Warden Herbarium
ETSU #13-0222


*Galax urceolata*
